                {
                    "id": "perfect_albedo_zero_temperature",
                    "description": "Degenerate boundary: R_p = 1.0 (perfect mirror — zero absorbed solar flux). Expected F_S = 0 exactly; the algebraic chain composes as T_e = (0 / sigma)^(1/4) = 0^(0.25) = 0 exactly in IEEE-754 (no NaN/Inf branch for zero base, principal-root convention), and F_L = sigma * 0^4 = 0 exactly. Anchors the all-zero limit of the absorbed-emitted balance and exercises the runner against the F_S = 0 corner where the (.)^(1/4) and (.)^4 ops both reduce to zero by IEEE-754 contract.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "S_0": 1370.0,
                        "R_p": 1.0
                    },
                    "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
                    "assertions": [
